# Ollama local model configuration

This directory contains an optional Ollama `Modelfile` for creating a project-specific local model wrapper.

## Create model

```bash
ollama create {{ project_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}-agent -f .ollama/Modelfile
```

## Run model

```bash
ollama run {{ project_name | lower | replace(' ', '-') }}-agent
```

## Notes

- Ollama itself does not read repository instruction files automatically.
- Tools such as OpenCode, OpenHands, Continue, or Cline must be configured to use the local Ollama endpoint.
- Default base URL: `{{ model.base_url | default('http://localhost:11434', true) }}`
